      "comment": "PINKY ROCKS (6) ran a blistering 25.46 winning over 455m at Murray Bridge last start. In winning form and can measure up again. KIA KEEPING (3) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind High Cube (30.31) in a Grade 3/4/5. Has the early speed to give a sight. Bold showing expected. WAY COOL (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three on end. Last start was checked in the run and finished third in a Grade 3/4/5 at this track (30.42). Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Has the ability and can measure up. ALL MUCKED UP (5) missed the placings when well supported last time – can make amends.",
